<section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
  <!-- Intro -->
  <div class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900">Getting Started</h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600 max-w-3xl">
      Welcome! If this is your first time here, don’t worry.
      This guide will walk you through everything step by step — from creating your account
      to publishing your very first blog post.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">

    <!-- Phase 1 -->
    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl border shadow-sm">
      <span class="text-sm font-semibold text-teal-600">Phase 1</span>
      <h3 class="mt-2 text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">Create Account</h3>
      <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600">
        To get started, you need to create an account.
        Click on the <strong>Sign Up</strong> or <strong>Register</strong> button and fill in your basic details
        like your name, email, and password.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600">
        After signing up, we’ll send you a verification email.
        Open your email and click the verification link to activate your account.
        Once this is done, you’ll be able to log in and access your dashboard.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Phase 2 -->
    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl border shadow-sm">
      <span class="text-sm font-semibold text-teal-600">Phase 2</span>
      <h3 class="mt-2 text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">Manage Profile</h3>
      <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600">
        After logging in, visit your profile section from the dashboard.
        This is where you can tell readers more about yourself.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600">
        You can update your profile photo, change your display name,
        write a short bio, and manage your account settings.
        Keeping your profile updated helps readers trust and recognize you.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Phase 3 -->
    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl border shadow-sm">
      <span class="text-sm font-semibold text-teal-600">Phase 3</span>
      <h3 class="mt-2 text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">First Blog</h3>
      <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600">
        Now comes the fun part — writing your first blog.
        Go to the dashboard and click on <strong>Create Blog</strong> or <strong>New Article</strong>.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600">
        Write your content using the editor, add images if needed,
        choose the right category, and publish your blog when you’re ready.
        Your article will be visible to readers immediately after publishing.
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>

  <!-- Closing -->
  <div class="mt-14 bg-teal-50 border border-teal-100 rounded-xl p-6">
    <p class="text-gray-700">
      That’s it! You’re all set.
      As people read and interact with your blogs, you’ll be able to track views,
      likes, and other activity directly from your dashboard.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
